article.headline: Duquesne 93, Winston-Salem 63
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Shawn James had 19 points, 12 rebounds and four blocked shots to lead Duquesne to a 93-63 victory over Winston-Salem State on Monday night. The victory was the Dukes' second over a Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference team to start the season. Duquesne (2-0) opened with a 129-59 rout of Howard on Friday. Phillip Fayne added 15 points, Damian Saunders scored 12 and Kieron Achara had 11 for Duquesne. McIntoche Alcius led Winston-Salem State (1-2) with 13 points. Isiah Tucker added 11 and Michael Puckett had 10. Duquesne broke open a close game with 4:50 left in the first half, turning a six-point lead into a 43-29 advantage at halftime. Fayne and Aaron Jackson combined to score the Dukes' first nine points of the second half, boosting the lead to 52-31. Duquesne maintained at least a 16-point lead the rest of the way. Duquesne outrebounded Winston-Salem State 49-33 and assisted on 21 of 31 baskets.
